# Plan: healthstack-patient-portal

Slug: healthstack-patient-portal
Date: 2026-06-14
Brief source: intake.out

---

## Demo Concept

**HealthStack Patient Portal** - a Sesame-style healthcare booking and dashboard
experience demonstrating Next.js/React architecture, Supabase-equivalent
role-based access (server-enforced via mw-backend JWT + RLS analogue), mocked
Stripe checkout, and HIPAA-aware design choices.

The demo shows two modes in one app: a patient flow and an admin flow. Visitors
can log in as either persona using credentials shown on the login screen and
experience genuinely different, permission-scoped data views.

---

## Prototype vs Full Decision

**LEAN FULL.**

All three trip conditions are clear:
1. Hero does NOT need a live third-party integration. Stripe checkout is mocked
   server-side. Supabase RLS is demonstrated via mw-backend role-gated endpoints.
2. Build is under 12 files, well within the 3-minute build cap.
3. The concept is interactive, not throwaway/visual.

No trip condition was triggered. Build full.

---

## Hero Feature

**Login -> Book appointment -> Mock Stripe checkout -> Role-scoped dashboards**

End-to-end patient flow:
1. Login screen with two visible persona buttons (Patient / Admin)
2. Service browser: 3-4 mock providers with specialties, ratings, and available
   slots (Sesame-style card grid)
3. Slot selection: pick a date/time, confirm booking
4. Mock Stripe checkout modal: card form UI, "Pay $95" button, returns confirmed
   payment (server-side mock returning fake PaymentIntent)
5. Booking confirmation screen + redirect to patient dashboard
6. Patient dashboard: only the logged-in patient's bookings, provider info,
   upcoming appointment card
7. Switch to Admin: admin dashboard shows all patients, all bookings, aggregate
   stats, access/audit log panel (who booked what, when viewed)

The role separation is server-enforced: the patient endpoint rejects admin tokens
and vice versa. This demonstrates the Supabase RLS analogue concretely.

---

## Supporting Features

1. **Mocked Stripe Checkout** - checkout modal with card input UI, POST to
   /healthstack/checkout, server returns fake confirmed PaymentIntent ID. UI
   shows masked card, amount, confirmation number.

2. **Role-scoped Admin Dashboard** - separate dashboard view with aggregate
   booking table, patient roster (initials-only for PHI minimization), and an
   access/audit log panel ("Patient Jane D. viewed records at 14:03"). Visible
   PHI minimization label in the UI.

---

## Decorative Elements (set dressing within hero, low-effort)

- Audit log panel in admin view (static mock entries, rendered from API response)
- "Secure Upload" affordance on patient dashboard: a file input with a lock icon
  and "End-to-end encrypted" label (stub upload endpoint exists on backend but UI
  does not require real file handling)
- HIPAA-aware note banner: small footer chip "Demo: PHI handling follows
  minimum-necessary principle"
- Lock icon + "TLS 1.3" chip in the header (visual trust signal)

