## Scope Fences

### In scope
- Login with role selection (patient + admin demo accounts)
- Service/provider browser (3-4 static providers seeded in backend)
- Slot booking (POST to backend, stored in-memory per session)
- Mock Stripe checkout (server returns fake PaymentIntent)
- Patient dashboard (own bookings only, role-gated)
- Admin dashboard (all bookings, access log, PHI-minimized roster)
- Secure upload affordance (stub)
- Design-token-aligned UI matching site aesthetic

### Out of scope
- Real Supabase project (demo simulates RLS via mw-backend JWT role check)
- Real Stripe (mocked server-side, framed explicitly in deck as "production uses
  real Stripe webhooks")
- Real Vercel deploy (demo hosted at michaelwegter.com/demos/healthstack-patient-portal/)
- HIPAA certification (addressed in proposal prose only, not built)
- Appointment cancellation, rescheduling, messaging

---

## Architecture

### Demo app (same-origin static)
Self-contained React app via CDN (React 18 + ReactDOM via esm.sh or unpkg,
no bundler). Vanilla ES modules. Renders inside a single index.html. Communicates
with mw-backend for auth, booking, and data.

**Why not a bundled Vite app:** The demo UI is straightforward enough that a CDN
React app avoids any build step and keeps the file count minimal. The stack story
(Next.js + Supabase in production) is explained in the deck, not simulated
exactly in the demo -- the demo proves the judgment and patterns, not the exact
toolchain.

### Backend (mw-backend)
New blueprint: healthstack_blueprint.py
- JWT-based auth with role claim (patient | admin)
- In-memory seeded data (no DB writes needed)
- Role-gated route guards on all data endpoints
- CORS open for site origin

### Portfolio wiring
- Add entry to src/data/workSamples.js (or create if not yet existing)
- Route: /work-samples/healthstack-patient-portal -> AppFrame iframing
  /demos/healthstack-patient-portal/
- Add "Work Samples" nav link if not present

