## File Manifest (10 files total, under 12-file cap)

### Demo (4 files)
```
../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/healthstack-patient-portal/
  index.html       <- app shell, CDN imports (React 18 via esm.sh)
  app.js           <- full React app: router, all views as components
  styles.css       <- design-token CSS (dark theme, mustard accent, Space Grotesk)
  api.js           <- fetch helpers: login(), getServices(), book(), checkout(),
                      getPatientDashboard(), getAdminDashboard()
```

### Backend (2 files, 1 edit)
```
../mw-backend/
  healthstack_blueprint.py   <- new Flask blueprint (clone of spotify_blueprint.py)
  server.py                  <- edit: add import + app.register_blueprint(healthstack_bp)
```

### Portfolio wiring (2-3 files)
```
../michaelwegter.com/src/data/workSamples.js   <- add registry entry (create if absent)
../michaelwegter.com/src/App.jsx               <- add /work-samples/:slug route if absent
../michaelwegter.com/src/components/Navbar.jsx <- add "Work Samples" link if absent
```

Total: 9-10 files. Well within cap.

