## Build Sequence (for demo-builder)

1. **Build healthstack_blueprint.py first** (backend must exist before demo can
   make real API calls during local testing)
   - Clone structure from spotify_blueprint.py
   - Seed: 2 users (patient + admin), 4 providers, 8 slots
   - Implement all 6 endpoints (login, services, book, checkout, patient dashboard,
     admin dashboard)
   - Register in server.py

2. **Build styles.css** using design tokens from CLAUDE.md. Key classes:
   - .hs-shell (full viewport, --bg-root background)
   - .hs-card (--bg-card, --border-default, border-radius 12px)
   - .hs-btn-primary (--mustard background, dark text)
   - .hs-btn-ghost (transparent, --border-default, --text-primary)
   - .hs-badge-admin (--hot-pink), .hs-badge-patient (--cyan-vivid)
   - .hs-table (for admin roster/audit log)
   - Provider cards with avatar circle, specialty label, rating stars

3. **Build api.js** - thin fetch wrappers
   - Base URL: https://api.michaelwegter.com/healthstack
   - All calls attach Authorization: Bearer <token> from localStorage
   - Exports: login, getServices, book, checkout, getPatientDashboard,
     getAdminDashboard, logout

4. **Build app.js** - React app with inline component definitions
   Views (use a simple hash-router or state-based router, no React Router needed):
   - LoginView: two persona buttons with credentials shown, POST /login
   - ServicesView: card grid of providers, "Book" button on each
   - SlotPickerView: date/time grid for selected provider
   - CheckoutView: mock card form, "Pay $95", POST /checkout, confirmation
   - PatientDashboardView: upcoming booking card, secure-upload stub, PHI note
   - AdminDashboardView: booking table, patient roster (initials), audit log panel
   - NavBar: logo "HealthStack", role badge, "Switch Account" link, logout
   State: { token, role, user, view, selectedProvider, selectedSlot, booking }

5. **Build index.html** - minimal shell
   - Imports React + ReactDOM from esm.sh
   - Loads styles.css and app.js as module
   - Single <div id="root"> mount point
   - Open Graph meta for nice link previews

6. **Wire portfolio**
   - Add workSamples.js entry (or append to existing)
   - Confirm /work-samples/:slug route via AppFrame exists in App.jsx
   - Add "Work Samples" to Navbar if missing

7. **Verify locally**: open /demos/healthstack-patient-portal/, log in as both
   personas, complete hero flow, check console for errors

